82}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After its Bastille Day appearance, the torch relay will visit Notre Dame Cathedral, the historic Sorbonne University and the Louvre Museum.\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorbonne\", \"score\": 0.8098957963809117, \"rank\": 0.20935341108823657, \"text\": \"Sorbonne University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorbonne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorbonne\"}, {\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louvre Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its Bastille Day appearance\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch relay\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre Dame Cathedral\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will then move on to other Paris landmarks on Monday.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.8559624563145145e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1711}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's Bastille Day celebrations offer Macron a moment of distraction from the political turmoil he unleashed with asnap electionthat weakened his centrist party and his presidency.The result left the country with a deadlocked parliamentand no one clearly in charge.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.117279595447976e-32, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This year's Bastille Day celebrations\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1751}, {\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1773}, {\"ngram\": \"distraction\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"the political turmoil\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"asnap electionthat\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"his centrist party\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"his presidency\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1899}, {\"ngram\": \"The result\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1927}, {\"ngram\": \"a deadlocked parliamentand\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 1984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The leftist alliance that won the most seats is struggling to agree on a candidate to replace Prime Minister Gabriel Attal, who could leave within days.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2096, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The leftist alliance\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"the most seats\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"a candidate\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is little sign of a ruling majority emerging from parliament, which is split into three loose camps.\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2246, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"little sign\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"a ruling majority\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"parliament\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"three loose camps\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2245}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Macron is barred by the constitution from calling new elections for a period of 12 months.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.117279595447976e-32, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the constitution\", \"from\": 2278, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"new elections\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"a period\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2334}, {\"ngram\": \"12 months\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, the European Union's second-largest economy, a nuclear-armed G7 power and a permanent member of the UN Security Council, is rudderless.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2376, \"end\": 2381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999995587150871, \"rank\": 1.2598890305146585e-07, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_of_Seven\", \"score\": 0.9999968899395003, \"rank\": 3.1100701145540615e-06, \"text\": \"G7\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_of_Seven\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_of_Sev